“network stability” means the ability of an electrical network to cope with -
* changes in the operational conditions including prolonged over voltage, faults, switching large loads  or generators on and off or lightning strikes; and
* network instability which may lead to the total loss of power to sections of the electrical network or to the entire electrical network;

